      ### JBoss Tools and Red Hat JBoss Developer Studio downloads
      **JBoss Tools** 4.1, 4.0, 3.3 and 3.2 are available in both the **FREE** and **Portfolio** Editions of **Red Hat JBoss Developer Studio** 7.x, 6.x, 5.x and 4.x, respectively. **Red Hat JBoss Developer Studio, Portfolio Edition** comes bundled with [Red Hat JBoss Enterprise Application Platform (JBoss EAP)](http://www.jboss.com/products/platforms/application/). If you want an easy to install and fully configured development environment, [try it out](http://devstudio.jboss.com/download/). Future development milestones will be available FREE as part of the [JBoss Developer Studio Early Access Program](http://devstudio.jboss.com/earlyaccess/).
  
      JBoss Tools is now splitted into two separate packages:
  
      - the **Core** version, which contains plugins for CDI, Hibernate, Web Services, OpenShift, AS, Central, Mobile, LiveReload, etc.
      - the **Integration Stack** (formerly **SOA**) version, which provides more specific plugins for BRMS (JBPM, Drools, etc.)
    
